ge of possible ways to tabulate and narrate the elemental as a way to bring into view fresh discussion on material constitutions and, thereby, new ethical stances, responsibilities, and power relations. In doing so, An Anthropogenic Table of Elements demonstrates through elementality that even the smallest and humblest stories are capable of powerful effects and vast journeys across time and space.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aNaturexEffect of human beings on. 0aPeriodic table of the elements. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Evolution.2bisacsh  aMendeleev.  aanthropocene.  abiology.  acarbon.  achemistry.  acultural anthropology.  aecology.  aelemental ecocriticism.  ahistory of science and technology.  alithium.  amold.  aperiodic table of elements.  ascience and technology studies.  avirus.1 aAddison, Courtney , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAddison, Courtney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBolman, Brad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChacko, Xan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCherkaev, Xenia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDesrochers-Turgeon, Émélie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElinoff, Eli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHelmreich, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeck, Frederic, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKenner, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLamoreaux, Janelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLatham, J. R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relato